PLUGINS USED:

pathogen
MRU
Grep
Command-t (need to install vim-nox for ruby support)
TagList
VCSCommand
surround
phpcomplete
lustyjuggler (need to install vim-nox for ruby support)
repeat
Tasklist
phpcs

=====================================

we need ctags:
go to root directory, run to create tags in each folder:
find * -type d -exec ~/.vim/gentags {} \;

run this one to build global tag file, contains only non-static tags:
ctags --verbose -f tags -h ".php" -R --exclude="\.svn" --totals=yes --tag-relative=yes --fields=+afkst --PHP-kinds=+cf-v --file-scope=no -R

=====================================

for taglist to work, in ~/.ctags, put this in (default params):
-R 
--exclude="\.svn" 
--totals=yes 
--tag-relative=yes 
--fields=+afkst 
--PHP-kinds=+cf-v 

=====================================

make svn ignore tags file in every folder. in ~/.subversion/config,

global-ignores = tags

=====================================
USAGE

grep: F3
MRU: :MRU
Command-t: ,t
VCS: VCSBlame, VCSLog --stop-on-copy, VCSUpdate (,cu), VCSVimDiff (,cv)
TagList: F8
surround: cs"- ("a word" to -a word-)
repeat: press . to repeat (meant to work with surround)
lustyjuggler: ,lj
toggle between paste mode: F2
edit vimrc: ,ev
reload vimrc: ,sv
Tasklist: ,td
to fold/unfold lines: visual select, then space to toggle display
phpcs: :Phpcs
phpcomplete: use omni

autocomplete: tab
autocomplete keyword: ctrl+x ctrl+p
autocomplete omni: ctrl+x ctrl+o

change color on the fly
:colo wombat
:color default

split window: ctrl+w s
vertically: ctrl+w v
navigate between windows:ctrl+h, ctrl+j, ctrl+k, ctrl+l
open file in split window - :sp file.php

